column36: Foliage colour: blue green. Flowers shape: cones
small bushes with tiny yellow flowers
Flowers, small, green or yellowish with 4 fused sepals but no petals
It grows between three and fifteen centimeters tall and has seated leaves with three lobes at the ends and small, white flowers.
The nodding flower is a violet with five purple petals. The lower three petals have white bases and purple veining.
column38: The flowers and leaves have long been used in various herbal remedies as poultices, laxatives, and to relieve cough and lung congestion. The Makah women used to eat the violet flowers and leaves during labor. The Klallam mashed the leaves and applied them to the chest or stomach to relieve pain.This is a hairy, compact plant growing from a small rhizome system. The leaves are spade- or heart-shaped, sometimes with broadly wavy margins.
